Now onto our next resort to enjoy the rest of the magic! social_posts.post_text: Character dining at Walt Disney World! To start off this series we are heading to Disney’s Wilderness Lodge to eat at Storybook Dining at Artist Point with Snow White. This chracter meal is more on the pricey end, and doesn’t have a ton of options if you or your children are picky eaters. However this meal is one of top picks and the characters are amazing! We rank this a 10/10! #disney #disneyworld #wdw #disneyvacation #characterdining #characterdiningatdisneyworld #snowwhite #familyvacation

Did you know that you can get your child’s first haircut in Walt Disney World? This is something special and fun to do to commemorate the special moment of a first haircut. The package is $28 it includes the haircut, Mickey ears, certificate and locket of hair. I highly recommend visiting Harmony Barbershop the next time your at Walt Disney World! #disney #wdw #waltdisneyworld #disneyvacation #harmonybarbershop #firsthaircut #disneytrip #disneyparks #magickingdom

Is Bibbidi Bobbidi Boutique Disney World worth the price tag? We paid for the Carriage package which included the makeover, a shirt, bag, the hair accessories, plus a full bottle of pixie dust nail polish! Our package cost $99 and we brought in our own princess dress to wear. We had Fairy Godmother Liz and she was beyond magical! If you are thinking about doing BBB it is 100% worth the price and magic! #disney #wdw #disneyworld #bibbidibobbidiboo #bibbidibobbidiboutique #disneyparks #disneycastmember #disneycast #disneyland #disneytrip #princess #disneyvacation #disneymagic #disneymagicmoments #fairygodmother

social_posts.post_text: Disney Animal Kingdom has so much to do. If you have toddlers or young children who love animals you have to get onto the Wildlife Express Train. This is a fun 10 minute train ride over to Rifiki’s Planet Watch.
